          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The 5 MV accelerator delivered proton and alpha-",
                "particle (4He+) beams with an intensity of up to 65",
                "microA on target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " An Inradoptics Scintinel cylindrical stilbene",
                "crystal 2 inches in diameter x 2 inches in length."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Beam-stop backings of Ta with a thickness of 0.5 mm",
                "were used for all targets. The primary target was one",
                "with deeply implanted 22Ne. The 22Ne targets were",
                "produced by implanting 22Ne ions onto a 0.5 mm thick",
                "Ta backing with a dosage of 300 mC over an area of 3",
                "cm2 at an energy of 200 keV. The distribution of the",
                "implanted 22Ne atoms in the Ta backing was measured",
                "using the well-known resonance in the 22Ne(p,gamma)",
                "23Na reaction at Elab = 1278 keV. Because of the",
                "implantation profile, a beam energy of Elab = 910 keV",
                "was required to reach the central portion of the",
                "thick-target yield plateau for the narrow Elab = 830",
                "keV resonance."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PSD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Stilbene has a lower scintillation efficiency",
                "than standard liquid scintillators but provides",
                "excellent pulse shape discrimination (PSD), which",
                "represents the detector's ability to discriminate",
                "between gamma-ray and neutron events at lower light",
                "output (i.e., neutron energy). This was critical for",
                "this experiment because, at the Elab = 830 keV",
                "resonance in the 22Ne(alpha,n)25Mg reaction,",
                "neutrons were produced with a maximum outgoing energy",
                "of En ~ 285 keV at 0 degree, well below the threshold",
                "of many types of standard liquid scintillators."
              ]
            }
          ],
